breaking in this house.

04:01.257 --> 04:03.191
Must be somebody new
to the neighborhood...

04:03.393 --> 04:05.190
...they gonna break in my house.

04:05.395 --> 04:08.262
I'm Madea,
and they gonna break in this house?

04:09.365 --> 04:10.389
Oh, hell no.

04:11.167 --> 04:12.794
Oh, see you later, Helmer.

04:15.138 --> 04:18.403
-Joe.
-Now roll the joint up.

04:22.378 --> 04:23.811
Joe.

04:24.847 --> 04:28.613
Mabel, what the hell wrong with you?
You don't be coming--

04:30.420 --> 04:32.047
Wake the hell up.

04:32.355 --> 04:34.084
You about to give me a heart attack.

04:34.290 --> 04:36.087
You too ugly
to be waking somebody up...

04:36.292 --> 04:38.385
...in the middle of the night,
I told you that.

04:38.594 --> 04:40.459
You gotta ease that ugly
up on people.

04:40.663 --> 04:42.631
You can't just show it to them
all at once.

04:42.832 --> 04:45.699
Code five, fool. Code five. Hurry up.

04:45.902 --> 04:48.632
-Get out the bed.
-Code five? Hell, go get them, Mabel.

04:48.838 --> 04:52.296
-Hell, you look like armed services.
-Hurry up.

04:52.508 --> 04:55.341
Ain't nothing in here but me.
This is your house.

04:57.847 --> 05:01.783
Wait a minute. My weed down there.
Oh, hell no now.

05:02.418 --> 05:05.410
Is this worth you getting
a cap busted in your ass for?

05:08.858 --> 05:11.793
-What the hell?
-Did they done drop my damn VCR?

05:12.595 --> 05:15.496
What you doing with my--?
Not your TiVo.

05:15.698 --> 05:18.531
Sit your ass down!
Wait, this is from me.

05:20.269 --> 05:22.533
Hold on, Joe. Hell.

05:25.508 --> 05:26.497
Them children.

06:25.968 --> 06:27.595
Clap your hands, girls!

06:31.474 --> 06:33.874
Y'all eating like y'all ain't ate nothing
in days.

06:34.077 --> 06:36.477
I don't know why the hell you feeding
these children.

06:36.679 --> 06:39.512
You feed them, they gonna
keep coming back, just like roaches.

06:39.715 --> 06:41.683
You got one roach,
you gonna have thousands.

06:41.884 --> 06:44.284
You never gonna be able
to get rid of these children.

06:44.487 --> 06:46.785
You ain't been able
to get rid of what you got.

06:49.725 --> 06:51.420
Scratch and sniff.

06:51.627 --> 06:56.121
Shut your mouth. I was in
a experiment with-- In Tuskegee.

06:56.332 --> 06:58.197
-You want some more sandwich?
-Yeah.

06:58.401 --> 07:01.461
-You say "yes, ma'am" to me.
-Yes, man.

07:03.573 --> 07:05.803
He say "yes, man."

07:06.776 --> 07:08.403
No, son, that ain't--

07:08.611 --> 07:10.875
That ain't no man.
She just look like one.

07:11.080 --> 07:13.412
-You say "yes, ma'am."
-What does that mean?

07:13.616 --> 07:15.846
Don't know what's wrong
with these children today.

07:16.052 --> 07:19.818
Ain't nobody teach you some respect?
"Yes, ma'am. No, ma'am. No, sir"?

07:20.022 --> 07:21.455
-Nobody teach you that?
-No.

07:21.657 --> 07:24.626
Somebody should've. I don't know
what's wrong with parents today.

07:25.261 --> 07:26.626
Hey, slow the hell down, boy.

07:26.829 --> 07:28.592
Wipe your mouth.
What the hell's wrong?

07:28.798 --> 07:31.130
-He crazy?
-No.

07:32.101 --> 07:33.363
What's wrong with him?

07:33.569 --> 07:35.537
-He's a weirdo.
-Eat your food and shut up.

07:35.738 --> 07:38.138
Girl, eat something.
Get you some butter and jelly.

07:38.341 --> 07:40.639
No, I'm good.
Just wanna make sure they eat.

07:40.843 --> 07:42.140
I'm mad as hell about my VCR.

07:42.345 --> 07:45.337
I'm trying to be nice to you,
but I'm mad as hell about this VCR.

07:45.548 --> 07:48.847
I ought to shank you.
This is my VCR.

07:49.051 --> 07:52.384
I had this VCR back in 1 973...

07:52.588 --> 07:55.386
...when Otis Redding came by
and he sat there with me...

07:55.591 --> 07:58.287
...and both of us watched
a movie on this VCR...

07:58.494 --> 08:00.359
...and you just drop it
like it's nothing.

08:00.563 --> 08:03.657
This is a antique, girl.
You know what a antique is?

08:03.866 --> 08:06.300
There one right there.
This is a antique.

08:06.502 --> 08:08.732
-Still gonna call the cops?
-Hell, yeah.

08:08.938 --> 08:11.964
You done broke in somebody's house.
Just because you looking sad...

08:12.175 --> 08:16.544
...you don't think nobody gonna call
the police? I'm calling the po-po.

08:16.746 --> 08:19.909
It's tore up, anyway. I don't see
no reason for you to call the cops.

08:20.116 --> 08:23.483
Don't tell me not to call the cops.
If I wanna call the cops, I'm gonna.

08:23.686 --> 08:25.984
I might not call
if you done learned your lesson.

08:26.189 --> 08:28.487
The lesson is simple.
You can ask people for stuff.

08:28.691 --> 08:30.659
You ain't gotta be
trying to steal nothing.

08:30.860 --> 08:33.192
I'm feeding you
out of the kindness of my heart.

08:33.395 --> 08:36.422
I'm doing the good Christian thing,
doing what Jesus would've did.

08:36.631 --> 08:38.691
I'm feeding you.
My daughter would be proud...

08:38.900 --> 08:41.369
...feeding the people
that came in here to steal.

08:41.571 --> 08:45.166
All this stuff going on in the world,
I can help y'all if you ask me to help.

08:45.374 --> 08:47.103
Ain't gotta come
breaking in the house.

08:47.310 --> 08:49.278
People are working hard
for what they got...

08:49.478 --> 08:51.537
...and you gonna break up
in somebody's house.

08:51.747 --> 08:54.238
-What's wrong with y'all?
-Hey, Big Bird, calm down.

08:54.450 --> 08:57.283
Making me upset, stealing
and break into somebody's house.

08:57.486 --> 08:59.852
-You hear me, boy?
-Yes, man.

09:05.394 --> 09:06.827
Boy, you're cute.

09:07.029 --> 09:09.224
He said it again.

09:10.933 --> 09:12.924
He said--

09:13.936 --> 09:17.269
You said it again.
Boy, you funny. You is funny.

09:17.473 --> 09:19.873
That ain't no man.
You can't say "yes, man."

09:20.076 --> 09:21.907
But that's what--

09:22.945 --> 09:24.606
Yes, ma'am. Yes, dude.

09:24.814 --> 09:25.872
As in, yes, sir.

09:26.082 --> 09:27.379
As in, yes, dude.

09:27.583 --> 09:29.608
As in, yes, bro.

09:29.819 --> 09:31.013
Where are your people?

09:31.220 --> 09:33.279
-My grandma--
-She's at work.

09:33.789 --> 09:35.222
Is that what you was gonna say?

09:35.424 --> 09:37.187
-No.
-Yes.

09:38.394 --> 09:41.761
-They lying.
-You know I can hear you, right?

09:42.832 --> 09:45.926
Let this child talk to me
before I choke you out.

09:49.372 --> 09:51.863
We haven't seen our grandma
in four days.

09:52.074 --> 09:53.371
Four days?

09:53.576 --> 09:54.873
Why? Is she on that stuff?

09:55.077 --> 09:56.977
No, she went to work
like she always do...

09:57.179 --> 09:58.874
...but this time,
she never came back.

09:59.081 --> 10:02.312
Manny, can you just shut up
and eat your food, please?

10:02.518 --> 10:04.645
This child can talk to me
if he want to.

10:04.854 --> 10:08.312
-Where your mom at?
-Dead. My grandma's at work.

10:08.524 --> 10:11.288
-Where's she work at?
-I don't know.

10:11.494 --> 10:14.793
-Y'all ain't got no living relative?
-We got an aunt.

10:15.331 --> 10:17.458
April. April.

10:18.467 --> 10:19.729
-Hey.
-Girl, wake up.

10:19.935 --> 10:22.426
I'm up. I'm here.

10:23.472 --> 10:24.905
Where did everybody go?

10:25.107 --> 10:28.076
Home. It's past closing.

10:28.744 --> 10:32.145
-Did Randy come get me?
-No, I ain't seen no Randy.

10:32.348 --> 10:34.111
Give me one more drink
while I wait.

10:34.317 --> 10:36.342
Girl, you had enough. Get up...

10:36.552 --> 10:39.214
-...and go now.
-lf you love me, give me another drink.

10:39.422 --> 10:41.447
I love you.
I can't give you another drink.

10:41.657 --> 10:43.887
Okay. All right. Okay.
I'm gone. I'm gone.

10:44.093 --> 10:45.355
-Have it your way.
-Hurry up.

10:45.561 --> 10:48.689
-Hey.
-Be careful.

10:51.334 --> 10:53.268
-Good night.
-Good night.

10:53.936 --> 10:55.631
-Oh, hey, April.
-Hey.

10:55.838 --> 10:57.567
You got some money?

10:57.773 --> 11:00.139
Man, didn't I just give you
some money?

11:00.343 --> 11:01.810
Yes, I did.

11:02.011 --> 11:03.205
Don't lie. Don't lie.

11:03.412 --> 11:06.848
Hey, hey! Hold it! Hold it!

11:07.049 --> 11:10.416
Man, superstar coming through.

11:24.200 --> 11:26.691
Should I get this? Wifey's calling.

11:26.902 --> 11:29.462
Shit, I wish you would.

11:29.672 --> 11:31.970
I dare you. Put it down.

11:32.174 --> 11:34.039
You need to fix
the floor in the bathroom.

11:34.243 --> 11:36.040
Everything in this damn house
is broken.

11:36.245 --> 11:38.907
Well, when I get some money to fix it,
I'll fix it.

11:39.115 --> 11:41.379
But until then,
what you get is raggedy.

11:41.884 --> 11:43.044
Who's snapping?

11:45.321 --> 11:46.982
Hello?

11:47.189 --> 11:48.781
Hey, baby.

11:51.026 --> 11:53.961
No. No, I ain't off--

11:55.297 --> 11:57.390
-You did? Stop.
-Stop.

11:57.600 --> 11:59.067
You what?

12:00.803 --> 12:03.033
Janice, I told you....

12:03.239 --> 12:06.868
No, I know that. Look, I'm happy.

12:07.076 --> 12:10.239
Look, I said I'm happy.
Yeah, okay. I'll call you later.

12:10.446 --> 12:14.212
-Yeah, you sound real happy.
-She's pregnant.

12:16.218 --> 12:17.242
Congratulations.

12:17.453 --> 12:21.355
April, you know good and damn well
I don't want no more kids.

12:21.557 --> 12:23.752
I can barely pay
the damn bills in my house.

12:24.393 --> 12:26.054
And yours.

12:26.796 --> 12:30.232
What the hell am I gonna do
with some more kids, huh?

12:30.433 --> 12:34.699
I got four already. I can't even handle
this damn child support.

12:34.904 --> 12:37.304
-Killing my ass.
-Whose fault is that?

12:38.474 --> 12:39.463
What did you say?

12:43.646 --> 12:45.045
Nothing.

12:45.247 --> 12:47.442
-You said something.
-Nothing. Baby, nothing.

12:47.650 --> 12:48.708
It's nothing.

12:48.918 --> 12:49.907
Nothing.

12:50.119 --> 12:51.313
-Nothing?
-No.

12:51.520 --> 12:53.545
What, you gonna tell me
you pregnant now?

12:53.756 --> 12:57.248
You know I don't want kids.
All I want is you.

12:57.460 --> 12:59.951
Well, good. Come on.

13:05.034 --> 13:06.899
-I gotta go.
-Okay.

13:07.102 --> 13:08.433
You know I love you, right?

13:09.071 --> 13:10.868
Me too.

13:11.707 --> 13:15.666
Now, go tell wifey I said hi.
Kiss the kids for me.

13:15.878 --> 13:19.837
-That's funny.
-I'm serious. Tell wifey I said hi.

13:20.516 --> 13:22.211
I'm going to sleep.

13:31.527 --> 13:33.017
This better be the right address.

13:33.229 --> 13:36.323
If I go one more place, and y'all
done sent me to the wrong place...

13:36.532 --> 13:39.968
...I'm gonna hurt somebody.
Get on out of the car, little boy.

13:40.169 --> 13:42.194
Come on, girl, with that attitude.

13:47.977 --> 13:50.707
You call that a knock?
Bang on the door and step down here.

13:58.654 --> 14:00.986
Somebody gonna open this door,
I don't care.

14:01.190 --> 14:04.250
-Okay!
-Kick the door, kick it.

14:04.460 --> 14:07.657
What the hell y'all banging my door
for at this time of the morning?

14:07.863 --> 14:09.057
It's 7 a.m.

14:09.265 --> 14:11.233
I don't know who you think
you talking to...

14:11.433 --> 14:13.958
...but it is 1 2:30 in the afternoon.

14:14.169 --> 14:16.569
-Do you know these children, hooker?
-No.

14:16.772 --> 14:18.330
Aunt April.

14:18.841 --> 14:20.172
Snitch.

14:20.376 --> 14:23.311
All right, that's my niece
and my nephews. What did y'all do?

14:23.512 --> 14:25.207
They broke into my house...

14:25.414 --> 14:27.473
...and broke my VCR
trying to steal something.

14:27.683 --> 14:29.708
I want my money.
That's why I brought them.

14:29.919 --> 14:31.580
These are not my kids.
You know what?

14:31.787 --> 14:34.688
-Take them to my mama.
-Hold the hell on.

14:34.890 --> 14:37.654
They ain't seen your mama
in four days.

14:38.427 --> 14:40.827
-That's not like her. Where is she?
-They don't know.

14:41.030 --> 14:43.863
Hell, why I'm supposed to know?
I don't know. I don't know her.

14:44.066 --> 14:46.762
Okay, my sister is dead.
Their mama, she dead.

14:46.969 --> 14:48.630
And so my mother is raising them...

14:48.837 --> 14:51.533
...and that's who you should talk to
to get your money.

14:51.740 --> 14:54.868
If she ain't there, you better get me
the $300 and get my VCR.

14:55.077 --> 14:56.339
That's all I'm telling you.

14:56.545 --> 14:59.605
I'm telling you I don't have $300,
and these ain't my kids.

14:59.815 --> 15:02.875
Let me explain something to you.
If you don't give me my money...

15:03.085 --> 15:05.519
...I'm calling the po-po
on all three of these thugs.

15:05.721 --> 15:07.120
You can use my phone.

15:07.323 --> 15:10.190
Help us, Aunt April.
We tried to find Grandma.

15:13.729 --> 15:15.594
What if I bring them
over to your house...

15:15.798 --> 15:17.390
...and they can work the money off?

15:17.600 --> 15:19.363
-Work it off? Hell, no.
-Clean up?

15:19.568 --> 15:21.433
-What do you mean "what"?
-No, no.

15:21.637 --> 15:24.401
I want my $300.
You gonna bring them to work for me?

15:24.607 --> 15:26.700
You can't bring them to my house
to do nothing.

15:26.909 --> 15:29.309
I got a white woman next door to me
and I have a dog.

15:29.511 --> 15:30.569
You know what that mean?

15:30.779 --> 15:34.044
I don't wanna let O.J.
and Michael Vick at my house.

15:34.416 --> 15:37.214
Well, I don't know what to tell you,
because I don't have--

15:37.419 --> 15:38.750
Fine. Fine.

15:38.954 --> 15:40.717
Make sure
they be over at my house.

15:40.923 --> 15:42.220
That thing ain't even worth--

15:42.424 --> 15:44.915
Say something else.
I want you to say something-- Say--

15:45.127 --> 15:48.426
Snatch away from me,
I'm gonna punch you like I dude.

15:48.631 --> 15:50.155
Say something.

15:52.167 --> 15:53.600
Come in here.

15:56.238 --> 15:59.207
Little O.J., that thug and
Sister Souljah, she know where I live.

15:59.408 --> 16:02.309
-Make sure they be at my house.
-Yeah.

16:05.080 --> 16:06.638
Where is your grandmother?

16:06.849 --> 16:08.976
-We don't know.
-Y'all can't stay here.

16:09.184 --> 16:11.049
Okay, I got a man,
and he don't like kids.

16:11.253 --> 16:13.483
So y'all gonna have
to figure something else out.

16:13.689 --> 16:16.590
All right, y'all can't stay here.
So where is she?

16:16.792 --> 16:18.760
You can't smoke around him.
He has asthma.

16:18.961 --> 16:21.759
Girl, this is my house.
You can wait outside.

16:21.964 --> 16:23.591
-Fine, then. We will.
-Good.

16:23.799 --> 16:27.667
Wait, we ain't been to sleep all night.
I'm tired.

16:27.870 --> 16:30.304
Well, y'all can stay here, but I'm out.

16:30.506 --> 16:34.567
Get up out of here with that attitude.
Come on. Get to stepping.

16:35.044 --> 16:37.604
-Hey, look, I'll see y'all later, okay?
-All right.

16:38.213 --> 16:39.305
-Bye-bye.
-Bye.

16:40.315 --> 16:43.307
Puffy and Biggie,
y'all don't wanna go with Lil' Kim?

16:44.253 --> 16:47.654
-Nope, I'm going to sleep.
-I'm going to bed. Y'all shut up.

16:47.856 --> 16:50.484
Don't make no noise.
I gotta work tonight.

16:53.629 --> 16:55.494
Oh, okay. Good.

16:55.698 --> 16:58.394
Bless you.
God bless you, and come again.

16:58.600 --> 17:00.192
Glad we could help.

17:02.271 --> 17:04.364
-Hi.
-Hello.

17:04.573 --> 17:07.633
I am from Pastor Hector Romalle's
church in Columbia.

17:07.843 --> 17:11.744
-You used to run missions there.
-That was a long time ago.

17:11.946 --> 17:15.007
-What's your full name?
-Sandino. Sandino Ramirez.

17:15.217 --> 17:18.414
You seemed to be doing so well there.
What are you doing here?

17:18.887 --> 17:21.412
I've come to this country
to find a better life.

17:21.623 --> 17:25.525
To find some work.
Not having much luck.

17:25.928 --> 17:28.726
I remember you're here,
I wanted to see if you could help me.

17:29.198 --> 17:32.395
Got any special skills?
What is it that you do?

17:33.235 --> 17:35.203
I'm a handyman.

17:35.404 --> 17:37.395
We have some things around
need to be fixed.

17:37.606 --> 17:40.871
Got plenty of tools,
plenty of supplies.

17:41.076 --> 17:43.374
Don't have much pay,
but we will pay you something.

17:43.579 --> 17:45.547
Stop! Come here!
Stupid, come here!

17:46.115 --> 17:48.606
-Deacon, Deacon, stop that girl.
-Hold on now.

17:48.817 --> 17:51.251
-Come here.
-Let go of me.

17:51.453 --> 17:53.250
If I ever catch you
in my store again--

17:53.455 --> 17:56.720
Miller, Miller, I got it.
I'm gonna take care of it.

17:56.925 --> 17:58.916
Hey, you'd better, pastor.

18:00.763 --> 18:03.732
-Young lady, are you on drugs?
-No. Why?

18:03.932 --> 18:06.457
-Where are your parents?
-I don't got no parents.

18:08.437 --> 18:09.426
Jennifer?

18:10.439 --> 18:12.532
-Miss Wilma.
-You know this child?

18:12.741 --> 18:14.368
Yeah.

18:14.576 --> 18:18.034
That's Rose's granddaughter.
She lives next door to me.

18:18.247 --> 18:20.545
Your grandmother's
a member of this church.

18:20.749 --> 18:22.614
-Well, have you seen her?
-Not in a while.

18:22.818 --> 18:25.286
-You don't know where she is?
-No.

18:25.487 --> 18:27.978
-You staying with April?
-No.

18:28.924 --> 18:32.416
Sister Wilma, take this man and show
him where we're having a problem.

18:32.628 --> 18:34.926
Sandino, I'm gonna work
on a place for you to stay.

18:35.130 --> 18:38.099
-Good seeing you again.
-Thank you. Good to see you too.

18:56.552 --> 18:58.315
Okay!

19:01.323 --> 19:02.347
Bullsh--

19:03.659 --> 19:05.024
Pastor.

19:05.627 --> 19:07.185
Hi, April.

19:08.397 --> 19:09.921
May we come in?

19:15.170 --> 19:18.401
-How are you, April?
-Sleepy. And you?

19:18.607 --> 19:21.041
All the better for seeing you.

19:21.243 --> 19:22.676
What did she do now?

19:22.878 --> 19:25.813
She was caught stealing
from the drugstore.

19:29.618 --> 19:30.846
Maybe she was hungry.

19:31.320 --> 19:33.481
Then why was she
