and I never spoke to her again.

49:45.732 --> 49:49.259
I said some things
I really wish I could take back.

49:57.210 --> 50:02.512
All the good she did for people
and she died on a bus.

50:04.017 --> 50:08.545
Oh, she was good to everybody.
She died on a bus alone.

50:15.796 --> 50:18.890
Watch out, y'all, stay close together.
I'm coming.

50:22.335 --> 50:24.326
Where have you been?

50:25.105 --> 50:27.403
Looking for Mama Rose.

50:31.645 --> 50:34.045
I have something to tell you.

50:34.614 --> 50:36.138
What is it?

50:40.220 --> 50:42.279
My mother died.

50:43.090 --> 50:44.489
What?

50:45.859 --> 50:47.383
Why are you lying?

50:48.895 --> 50:49.884
She's not lying.

50:50.097 --> 50:52.190
You will say anything
to get rid of us, huh?

50:52.399 --> 50:54.731
-Jennifer.
-lf you don't want us here, we'll go.

50:54.935 --> 50:56.368
You don't have to say all that.

50:58.138 --> 51:00.231
-It's not true.
-You will say anything.

51:00.440 --> 51:03.238
-lt is true, Manny.
-Can I go feed them?

51:04.578 --> 51:09.208
-Yeah.
-Jennifer. Jennifer.

51:10.550 --> 51:11.539
Are you okay?

51:12.285 --> 51:14.310
Yeah, I'm fine. People die. So what?

51:14.521 --> 51:17.046
Hey, listen,
it's okay to cry or to be upset.

51:17.257 --> 51:19.020
I said I'm fine, okay?

51:36.409 --> 51:39.207
Yo, turn the damn TV down, please.

51:40.680 --> 51:42.170
Hey, Agnes, how you doing?

51:42.382 --> 51:44.816
-Good to see you.
-Hi, Madea.

51:46.720 --> 51:48.415
What you doing sitting out here?

51:49.356 --> 51:50.823
Trying to steal something?

51:56.096 --> 51:57.859
What's going on with you?

51:59.599 --> 52:00.964
My grandmother died.

52:01.168 --> 52:03.136
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that, babe.

52:03.336 --> 52:06.863
My Aunt April's gonna send us
back to foster care.

52:07.374 --> 52:08.932
They're going to separate us.

52:10.811 --> 52:12.244
I'm all Manny and Byron got.

52:12.445 --> 52:16.245
If we separate, I don't know--
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

52:16.716 --> 52:19.617
-Oh, no.
-Calm yourself down, honey.

52:19.820 --> 52:22.914
-Calm down. Getting all worked up.
-Can we stay with you?

52:27.828 --> 52:29.659
Nobody wants us.

52:29.863 --> 52:35.130
-That ain't true. Somebody wants you.
-I'm only 1 6. I'm....

52:36.269 --> 52:39.670
-I don't know how to handle all this.
-Honey.

52:39.873 --> 52:42.501
-I'm tired. I don't--
-Living takes a lifetime.

52:42.709 --> 52:45.542
You got a whole lot more living
to do, honey.

52:45.745 --> 52:49.112
I don't feel like I'm gonna--
I don't feel like I'm gonna make it.

52:49.316 --> 52:50.840
You gonna make it. Hush, dear.

52:51.051 --> 52:53.451
Gotta keep getting up every day,
one day at a time.

52:53.653 --> 52:54.711
You're gonna make it.

52:54.921 --> 53:00.655
My Grandma Rose used to tell us
to pray about it, and if....

53:01.361 --> 53:05.388
Then that's what you ought to do,
pray about it, talk to the Lord about it.

53:05.599 --> 53:10.696
Yeah, but she only told us--
She never told me how to do it.

53:12.839 --> 53:14.136
Would you teach me?

53:15.976 --> 53:17.204
Please.

53:17.844 --> 53:20.574
-Show you how to pray?
-Yeah.

53:22.282 --> 53:23.874
Oh, child, I ain't talked to God...

53:24.084 --> 53:27.747
...since the last time I saw a cop
in my rearview mirror.

53:29.389 --> 53:31.323
I guess I can try.

53:31.524 --> 53:33.856
I can try to pray.
You know the number?

53:34.060 --> 53:35.049
The what?

53:35.262 --> 53:36.593
-The number.
-The number?

53:36.796 --> 53:38.354
To call him.

53:38.565 --> 53:41.261
They say "Jesus On the Mainline."
I don't know the number.

53:41.468 --> 53:42.992
Sit back, sit back.

53:43.203 --> 53:45.865
Okay, bow your head.

53:46.172 --> 53:50.108
First, giving honor to God,
to the head of my life.

53:53.280 --> 53:57.842
Father

53:58.051 --> 54:01.145
I stretch

54:01.621 --> 54:08.083
My hand

54:10.196 --> 54:11.288
